(169,	1,	'2015-06-02 06:14:33',	'2015-06-02 06:14:33',	'<h1>Temperature Qualification</h1>\r\n<p>Temperature qualification  is the process of qualifying and certification of assets which are used for critical applications. This ensures  that the tested item is capable of maintaining the specified critical parameters throughout the entire area under normal operating conditions. Such a test and certification will provide an insight into the performance aspects of the equipment or the enclosed area.</p>\r\n<p>Temperature is a major parameter to be tested for qualifying an equipment. However this need not be the only parameter or the main parameter to be tested depending on the application and type of equipment. In the article we mainly explain about Temperature Qualification.</p>\r\n<h1>What is Difference between Mapping study and Qualification?</h1>\r\n<p>This is often a subject of confusion and can be simply explained. In brief terms, qualification is much more elaborate process than a mapping study. A mapping study only analyzes the distribution of temperature and humidity if applicable and the result will show whether the distribution is uniform. Mapping study is only one part of the qualification process. The qualification procedure has lot of other verification and test to check whether all the major equipment are installed and being operated properly so that they are capable of achieving the desired temperature and humidity. eg. If a cold room is qualified for 1-8 Deg C, it means that the entire cold room and associated machines are capable of maintaining the temperature of 2-8C. Nowadays all international pharmaceutical companies prefer  their distributors to have qualification for their critical assets such as cold rooms, vans, boxes etc.</p>\r\n',	'temperature-qualification',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'130-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-06-02 06:14:33',	'2015-06-02 06:14:33',	'',	130,	'http://www.vackerglobal.com/130-revision-v1/',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
